          "author": "descript",
          "authorName": "Descript",
          "text": "Every webinar, someone asks Marcello how he uses Underlord. Every webinar, his eye twitches a little harder. So we hit record while he answered this time. Here's exact 6-step prompt he runs through Underlord on every video, before he touches a single thing himself: 1. Studio Sound @ 80% intensity — dialed in for his recording room (100% scrubs too much life out) 2. Remove filler words but KEEP \"like\" — he spot-checks those himself because half the time he means them 3. Remove retakes — \"if there's a retake, I don't need it\" 4. Apply Eye Contact — he reads a teleprompter every time, so this fixes the off-camera gaze 5. Split into chapters 6. Apply his custom \"Marcello\" layout pack — instant on-brand All six bundled into one saved prompt, run on Underlord with Opus 4.7, the moment media is imported. Then he does the creative \"last 20%\" by hand.",
